Dependencies:

- Nvidia OptiX 2.0 - http://developer.nvidia.com/object/optix-home.html
- gcc >= 4.5.0 - http://gcc.gnu.org
- boost >= 1.44 - http://www.boost.org
- OpenMesh >= 2.0-RC5 - http://www.openmesh.org/
- FLTK >= 1.1 - http://www.fltk.org
- CUDA SDK >= 3.2 - http://developer.nvidia.com/object/cuda_3_2_downloads.html
- Glew >= 1.5.6 - http://glew.sourceforge.net/
- cmake >= 2.8.1 - http://www.cmake.org

To compile, enter in the appropriate directory and type:

cmake .
make

The executable will be in src/rtgpu

To rotate the camera, hold the left mouse button while moving mouse pointer.
To rotate the light in the teapot scene, hold the middle mouse button while
moving the mouse pointer

In OptiX project, to change the render method, change the appropriate #define
in src/matte.cu

To change the scene rendered (teapot or sponza), change the appropriate #define
in src/canvas.cpp

